"PROTECT: Policy and Commercial &#xa0;BIS SELECT COMMITTEE INQUIRY INTO ROYAL MAIL PRIVATISATION&#xa0;HM GOVERNMENT EVIDENCE PAPER&#xa0;&#xa0;BACKGROUND: The Universal Postal Service&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRATIONALE: The Need for Reform&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nACCESS TO PRIVATE CAPITAL AND COMMERCIAL DISCIPLINES&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWHAT GOVERNMENT HAS ANNOUNCED&#xa0;“The Government will secure the universal postal service for the benefit of all users by securing Royal Mail’s future through the introduction of private sector capital and associate disciplines. \nThis will be achieved through:\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ndelivering a sale of shares in Royal Mail within this Parliament;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncreating an employee share scheme that, as Parliament has decided, will lead to at least 10% of the company in employee ownership, to drive stronger staff engagement; and\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ndelivering a financial outcome for the taxpayer, which when considered in the context of the overarching policy objective, represents overall value for money.”\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nThe institutional offer and the retail offer opened on 27 September \nand are \nexpected to close on 8 October 2013. Conditional dealings are expected to commence on 11 October and Admission to the London Stock Exchange is expected to take place on 15 October.\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nHMG intends to dispose of a majority stake including, leaving HMG with a residual holding between 30%. and 49.9%. \nThe\n \nBase \nOffer \nsize will be \nbetween 40.1 per cent. and 52.2 per cent. of Royal Mail’s share capital\n, with additional s\nhares representing up to 15 per cent. of the Base Offer also being made available \nthrough\n \no\nver\n-allotment Arrangements.\n \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nIn addition\n,\n 10 per cent of Royal Mail shares will be made available for free to around 150,000 eligible UK-based Royal Mail employees under the Employee Share Scheme. \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nThe e\nxpected\n Offer price range \nis \n260p to 330p per Share, implying a market capitalisation on Admission of between £2,600 million and £3,300 million.\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nHM Government currently envisages that around 70 per cent. of the Base Offer will be allocated to institutional investors.\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nThe \nIPO\n includes a Retail offer\n, enabling \nmembers of the public\n located in the \nUK\n to apply for shares through intermediaries or \ndirect to Government\n. The minimum application size for members of the public is £750. Eligible Royal Mail employees can apply through the \nEmployee Priority Offer\n which has a minimum application size of £500. \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nRoyal Mail intends to propose a final dividend only, to be paid in July 2014, of £133 million. In subsequent financial years Royal Mail intends to pursue a progressive dividend policy having regard to the normalised earnings progression of the Group. \n&#xa0;\nSAFEGUARDS&#xa0;The Universal Postal Service&#xa0;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ndelivery of letters six days per week to every address in the \nUK\n (parcels five days per week) at uniform and affordable prices; and \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nf\nree services for the blind.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;The Post Office &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRELATED DOCUMENTS&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nReport to Parliament: Royal Mail \nSale\n of Shares, 10 July 2013 \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nIntention to Float announcement, 12 September 2013 \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nPrice\n \nRange\n and Offer Launch announcement, 27 September 2013 \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nRoyal Mail Prospectus, 27 September 2013 \n&#xa0;\n4\n&#xa0;\n Ofcom Communications Market Report 2012 – August 2013 - \nhttp://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/binaries/research/cmr/cmr13/2013_UK_CMR.pdf\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/211669/bis-13-1054-royal-mail-sale-of-shares.pdf\n “\nModernise or decline: policies to maintain the universal postal service in the \nUnited Kingdo\nm\n”\n – Hooper, Hutton, Smith – December 2008 - \nhttp://www.berr.gov.uk/files/file49389.pdf\n “Saving the Royal Mail’s universal postal service in the digital age” – Hooper – September 2010 - \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/31808/10-1143-saving-royal-mail-universal-postal-service.pdf\n Royal Mail preliminary results for the year ended 31 March 2013 – May 2013 - \nhttp://www.royalmailgroup.com/sites/default/files/Royal%20Mail%20Preliminary%20Results%202012-13_A_version.pdf\n https://www.gov.uk/government/news/royal-mail-announcement-of-intention-to-float\n https://www.gov.uk/government/news/royal-mail-share-offer\n http://www.royalmailgroup.com/sites/default/files/161763%20Project%20PNF%20Full%20Prospectus.pdf\n Business, Innovation and Skills Committee, 15\nth\n Report, Stamp Prices, 1 March 2013\n End-to-end competition in the postal sector – Ofcom -  27 March 2013 - \nhttp://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/e2e-guidance/statement/\n"